<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName LSID="8C558AA3-011E-58A4-856B-5C9D1E83F07D" authority="Skottsb." authorityName="Skottsb." class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Micrastelia" species="waialealae" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Micrastelia Skottsb.</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Micrastelia" species="waialealae" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Micrastelia</taxonomicName>
Skottsb., Kongl. Svenska Vetenskapsakad. Handl. ser. 3, 14(2): 56. 1934.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
Low, compact, turf forming growth form; leaves caniculate; inflorescence bearing few flowers; staminate flowers with short filaments (0.6-1.9 mm); pistillate flowers with short outer tepals (2.6-3.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.8-1.3 mm); ovary trilocular, intermediate length (2.6-3.8 mm); fruit ellipsoid, many seeds per fruit (17-24); seeds short and narrow (1.1-1.7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.5-0.8 mm). Type: 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Forst.) Gaudich.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
The relationships of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Micrastelia" species="pumila" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Micrastelia</taxonomicName>
are poorly resolved, with alternate relationships with 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
and the clade containing 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Tricella) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Tricella" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Tricella</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Skottsberg, 1934" authorityName="Birch" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteliaceae" genus="Collospermum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Collospermum" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Collospermum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Birch unpublished PhD thesis 2011, 
<bibRefCitation author="Birch, JL" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="117" pagination="102 - 115" publicationUrl="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" refId="B2" refString="Birch, JL, Keeley, SC, Morden, CW, 2012. Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s.l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 65: 102 - 115, DOI: 10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" title="Molecular phylogeny and dating of Asteliaceae (Asparagales): Astelia s. l. evolution provides insight into the Oligocene history of New Zealand." url="10.1016/j.ympev.2012.05.031" volume="65" year="2012">Birch et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Microastelia" species="pumila" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Microastelia</taxonomicName>
contains a single species, 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a compact, turf-forming plant and dominant component of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
moorland in Chile, the Falkland Islands, and Tierra del Fuego. As a cushion-forming species, it differs morphologically from 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
, which contains species with open, spreading growth form that are epiphytic or terrestrial and primarily found of the understory in lowland to montane forests. 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does share morphological features with 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Asteliopsis) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Asteliopsis" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Asteliopsis</taxonomicName>
(e.g. short pistillode or pistil) and, alternatively, with 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Collospermum) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Collospermum" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Collospermum</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia (Tricella) subsp. subg." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subGenus" species="pumila" subGenus="Tricella" subSpecies="subg.">Astelia subg. Tricella</taxonomicName>
(e.g. seeds with a short, truncate funicle). The subgeneric placement of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia subsp. sect." order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Micrastelia" species="pumila" subSpecies="sect.">Astelia sect. Micrastelia</taxonomicName>
remains equivocal and the section is unplaced (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">incertae sedis</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="included species and distribution">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Included species and distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">
Chile, Falkland Islands, Tierra del Fuego: 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Liliaceae" genus="Astelia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Astelia pumila" order="Asparagales" pageId="10" pageNumber="115" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pumila">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Astelia pumila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Forst.) Gaudich.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="115" type="habitat">
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="10" pageNumber="115">Lowland (low latitudes) to sub-alpine (mid and higher latitudes) herbfields particularly on wet substrates (seeps, swamps etc.).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
